{"title_page": "Brandon Cronenberg", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian writer and film director|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Brandon Cronenberg''' (born circa 1980<ref name=BookNerd>{{cite web |url= http://www.canada.com/entertainment/book+nerd+cinephile+says+Cronenberg/7218147/story.html |title=I was a 'book nerd' not a cinephile, says Cronenberg son |first= Jay|last= Stone|work=canada.com |date= 2012-09-10|accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref>) is a Canadian writer and film director. He is the son of acclaimed director [[David Cronenberg]]. He studied film at [[Ryerson University]] in [[Toronto]], Canada. He initially considered himself to be a \"book nerd\" growing up, who was interested in becoming a writer, painter or musician. He came to realize that film contained all those elements and attended film school.<ref name=\"BookNerd\" />\n\nHis first feature film ''[[Antiviral (film)|Antiviral]]'' debuted at the [[2012 Cannes Film Festival]] in the ''[[Un Certain Regard]]'' section.<ref name=\"Official Selection\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/article/58878.html |title=2012 Official Selection |accessdate=2012-04-21 |work=Cannes}}</ref><ref name=\"torontosun\">{{cite web |url=http://www.torontosun.com/2012/04/19/cannes-seeing-double-cronenbergs |title=Cannes seeing double Cronenbergs |accessdate=2012-04-21 |work=Toronto Sun}}</ref> Cronenberg re-edited the movie after the festival to make it tighter, trimming nearly six minutes out of the film. The revised film was first shown at the 2012 [[Toronto International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.torontosun.com/2012/09/09/brandon-cronenberg-brings-first-feature-film-antiviral-home |title=Brandon Cronenberg brings first feature film 'Antiviral' home|first= Bruce|last= Kirkland|work=torontosun.com |date= 2012-09-09|accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref> Cronenberg's next film ''[[Possessor (film)|Possessor]]'' stars [[Christopher Abbott]], [[Andrea Riseborough]], [[Jennifer Jason Leigh]], [[Stacy Martin]] and [[Sean Bean]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/berlin-sean-bean-jennifer-jason-leigh-stacy-martin-board-sci-fi-thriller-possessor-1184699|title=Berlin: Sean Bean, Jennifer Jason Leigh, Stacy Martin Board Sci-Fi Thriller 'Possessor'|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Alex|last=Ritman|date=February 10, 2019|accessdate=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Antiviral (film)|Antiviral]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Please Speak Continuously and Describe Your Experiences as They Come to You]]'' (2019; short film)\n* ''[[Possessor (film)|Possessor]]'' (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0188722}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cronenberg, Brandon}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Canadian male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Writers from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian screenwriters]]\n\n\n{{Canada-film-director-stub}}\n{{Canada-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian writer and film director|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Brandon Cronenberg''' (born circa 1980<ref name=BookNerd>{{cite web |url= http://www.canada.com/entertainment/book+nerd+cinephile+says+Cronenberg/7218147/story.html |title=I was a 'book nerd' not a cinephile, says Cronenberg son |first= Jay|last= Stone|work=canada.com |date= 2012-09-10|accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref>) is a Canadian writer and film director. He is the son of acclaimed director [[David Cronenberg]]. He studied film at [[Ryerson University]] in [[Toronto]], Canada. He initially considered himself to be a \"book nerd\" growing up, who was interested in becoming a writer, painter or musician. He came to realize that film contained all those elements and attended film school.<ref name=\"BookNerd\" />\n\nHis first feature film ''[[Antiviral (film)|Antiviral]]'' debuted at the [[2012 Cannes Film Festival]] in the ''[[Un Certain Regard]]'' section.<ref name=\"Official Selection\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/article/58878.html |title=2012 Official Selection |accessdate=2012-04-21 |work=Cannes}}</ref><ref name=\"torontosun\">{{cite web |url=http://www.torontosun.com/2012/04/19/cannes-seeing-double-cronenbergs |title=Cannes seeing double Cronenbergs |accessdate=2012-04-21 |work=Toronto Sun}}</ref> Cronenberg re-edited the movie after the festival to make it tighter, trimming nearly six minutes out of the film. The revised film was first shown at the 2012 [[Toronto International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.torontosun.com/2012/09/09/brandon-cronenberg-brings-first-feature-film-antiviral-home |title=Brandon Cronenberg brings first feature film 'Antiviral' home|first= Bruce|last= Kirkland|work=torontosun.com |date= 2012-09-09|accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref> Cronenberg's next film ''[[Possessor (film)|Possessor]]'' stars [[Christopher Abbott]], [[Andrea Riseborough]], [[Jennifer Jason Leigh]], [[Stacy Martin]] and [[Sean Bean]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/berlin-sean-bean-jennifer-jason-leigh-stacy-martin-board-sci-fi-thriller-possessor-1184699|title=Berlin: Sean Bean, Jennifer Jason Leigh, Stacy Martin Board Sci-Fi Thriller 'Possessor'|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Alex|last=Ritman|date=February 10, 2019|accessdate=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Antiviral (film)|Antiviral]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Please Speak Continuously and Describe Your Experiences as They Come to You]]'' (2019; short film)\n* ''[[Possessor (film)|Possessor]]'' (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0188722}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cronenberg, Brandon}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people